sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Group.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new Group. Grouping is not supported for custom layouting. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getHeaderCheckBoxState headerCheckBoxState} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.HeaderCheckboxState (default: Hidden)
    • {@link #getKey key} : string
    • {@link #getCollapsed collapsed} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getIcon icon} : string
    • {@link #getMinWidth minWidth} : float (default: undefined)
    • {@link #getParentGroupKey parentGroupKey} : string
  • Aggregations
  • Events
    • {@link #event:headerCheckBoxPress headerCheckBoxPress} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:collapseExpand collapseExpand} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:showDetail showDetail} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.ElementBase#constructor sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.ElementBase} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.Sim.description: A simple shape that consists of a single SVG shape.
sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.Sim.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new SimpleShape. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getStrokeWidth strokeWidth} : float (default: 0.25)
    • {@link #getStrokeColor strokeColor} : sap.m.ValueCSSColor (default: Neutral)
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.Shape#constructor sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.Shape} can be used as well.
sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.Sim.helpDescription: A simple shape that consists of a single SVG shape.

fullAnimationDuration.description:
Deprecated! Since 1.54.1 All animations are now limited to 250 ms.
Specifies the duration, in milliseconds, of the animation that would fill an empty shape to the full. The actual time it takes to change the shape's filling is proportional to the difference between the initial and the target status indicator's value. For example, a change from 20 percent to 70 percent takes only half of the time specified in the fullAnimationDuration property. If this property is set to 0, changes are applied instantly without any animation.

DeprecatedInfo.description: All animations are now limited to 250 ms.

fillingAngle.description:
Defines the angle at which the shape is filled. This property overrides the fillingDirection property.
Accepted values include 0 through 360 degrees.
For example, if you set the filling angle to 45, the shape will be filled diagonally from the lower right part of the shape to its upper left part.
This property can be used only when {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.FillingType} is set to Linear.

sap.suite.ui.commons.BusinessCard.description: This control allows you to display business card information including an image, first title (either URL link or text), second title, and multiple text lines.
sap.suite.ui.commons.BusinessCard.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new BusinessCard. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getType type} : string
    • {@link #getIconPath iconPath} : sap.ui.core.URI
    • {@link #getSecondTitle secondTitle} : string
    • {@link #getWidth width} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize
    • {@link #getImageTooltip imageTooltip} : string
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getContent content} : sap.ui.core.Control
    • {@link #getFirstTitle firstTitle} : sap.ui.core.Control
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.
sap.suite.ui.commons.BusinessCard.helpDescription:
Deprecated! Since 1.32 Deprecated. Standard Fiori technology should be used.

sap.suite.ui.commons.MicroProcessFlow.description:
The MicroProcessFlow control can be used to track the progress of a process.
It is best used for linear processes, such as document, order, and approval flows, and can be embedded in tiles, tables, and other containers.

To display more complex processes and workflows, use {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlow} instead.
sap.suite.ui.commons.MicroProcessFlow.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new MicroProcessFlow. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getAriaLabel ariaLabel} : string
    • {@link #getRenderType renderType} : sap.suite.ui.commons.MicroProcessFlowRenderType (default: Wrap)
    • {@link #getWidth width} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: )
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getContent content} : sap.suite.ui.commons.MicroProcessFlowItem[]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

The MicroProcessFlow control can be used to track the progress of a process.
It is best used for linear processes, such as document, order, and approval flows, and can be embedded in tiles, tables, and other containers.

To display more complex processes and workflows, use {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlow} instead.

sap.suite.ui.commons.DateRangeSlider.description: The Date Range Slider provides the user with a Range Slider control that is optimized for use with Dates.
sap.suite.ui.commons.DateRangeSlider.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new DateRangeSlider. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getWidth width} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 100%)
    • {@link #getEnabled enabled} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getEditable editable} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getVisible visible} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowBubbles showBubbles} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getSmallStepWidth smallStepWidth} : float
    • {@link #getTotalUnits totalUnits} : int
    • {@link #getStepLabels stepLabels} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getLabels labels} : string[]
    • {@link #getMin min} : object
    • {@link #getMax max} : object
    • {@link #getValue value} : object
    • {@link #getValue2 value2} : object
    • {@link #getPinGrip pinGrip} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getPinGrip2 pinGrip2} : boolean (default: false)
  • Events
    • {@link #event:change change} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:liveChange liveChange} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.Pat.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new Path. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getD d} : string
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.SimpleShape#constructor sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.SimpleShape} can be used as well.

fullAnimationDuration.description:
Deprecated! Since 1.54.1 All animations are now limited to 250 ms.
Specifies the duration, in milliseconds, of the animation that would fill an empty shape to the full. The actual time it takes to change the shape's filling is proportional to the difference between the initial and the target status indicator's value. For example, a change from 20 percent to 70 percent takes only half of the time specified in the fullAnimationDuration property. If this property is set to 0, changes are applied instantly without any animation.
fullAnimationDuration.helpDescription:
Deprecated! Since 1.54.1 All animations are now limited to 250 ms.
Specifies the duration, in milliseconds, of the animation that would fill an empty shape to the full. The actual time it takes to change the shape's filling is proportional to the difference between the initial and the target status indicator's value. For example, a change from 20 percent to 70 percent takes only half of the time specified in the fullAnimationDuration property. If this property is set to 0, changes are applied instantly without any animation.

DeprecatedInfo.description: All animations are now limited to 250 ms.

fillingAngle.description:
Defines the angle at which the shape is filled. This property overrides the fillingDirection property.
Accepted values include 0 through 360 degrees.
For example, if you set the filling angle to 45, the shape will be filled diagonally from the lower right part of the shape to its upper left part.
This property can be used only when {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.FillingType} is set to Linear.

sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilder.description:
Calculation Builder allows you to perform arithmetic calculations on constants and variables using standard arithmetic operators as well as most common logical operators and functions.
You can customize the sets of variables and functions that are visible in the calculation builder and introduce your own custom functions, as needed.
Arithmetic expressions can be entered using a touch-friendly visual editor or a textual editor that provides autocomplete suggestions for variables and checks the expression syntax as you type.
sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilder.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new calculation builder. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getExpression expression} : string
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getShowToolbar showToolbar} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getWrapItemsInExpression wrapItemsInExpression} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getLayoutType layoutType} : string (default: Default)
    • {@link #getShowInputToolbar showInputToolbar} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getReadOnly readOnly} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getAllowComparisonOperators allowComparisonOperators} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getAllowLogicalOperators allowLogicalOperators} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getAllowSuggestions allowSuggestions} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getAllowStringConstants allowStringConstants} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getValidationMode validationMode} : sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderValidationMode (default: LiveChange)
    • {@link #getDisabledDefaultTokens disabledDefaultTokens} : string (default: )
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getItems items} : sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderItem[] (default)
    • {@link #getVariables variables} : sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderVariable[]
    • {@link #getFunctions functions} : sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderFunction[]
    • {@link #getOperators operators} : sap.ui.core.Item[]
    • {@link #getGroups groups} : sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderGroup[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:validateFunction validateFunction} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:change change} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:afterValidation afterValidation} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.
sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilder.helpDescription:
Calculation Builder allows you to perform arithmetic calculations on constants and variables using standard arithmetic operators as well as most common logical operators and functions.
You can customize the sets of variables and functions that are visible in the calculation builder and introduce your own custom functions, as needed.
Arithmetic expressions can be entered using a touch-friendly visual editor or a textual editor that provides autocomplete suggestions for variables and checks the expression syntax as you type.

sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowLaneHead.description: This control gives you an overview of documents or items used in a process flow. The process flow is represented by donut chart sections that are colored according to the status of documents. This control can be used in two different ways. If you use it standalone, an event is triggered and can be caught to display the node map. If you use it with nodes or documents, it gives you an overview of the documents or items used in the process flow, which is represented by the donut chart sections.
sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowLaneHead.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ProcessFlowLaneHeader. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getText text} : string
    • {@link #getIconSrc iconSrc} : sap.ui.core.URI
    • {@link #getPosition position} : int
    • {@link #getLaneId laneId} : string
    • {@link #getState state} : object
    • {@link #getZoomLevel zoomLevel} : sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowZoomLevel
  • Events
    • {@link #event:press press} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.
sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowLaneHead.helpDescription: This control gives you an overview of documents or items used in a process flow. The process flow is represented by donut chart sections that are colored according to the status of documents. This control can be used in two different ways. If you use it standalone, an event is triggered and can be caught to display the node map. If you use it with nodes or documents, it gives you an overview of the documents or items used in the process flow, which is represented by the donut chart sections.

weight.description:
Weight of the fillable shape, relative to other fillable shapes included in this custom shape. This property allows you to distribute the status indicator's value between distinct SVG shapes included in the custom shape. For example, for four SVG shapes with weights 1, 2, 3, and 4 (total weight 10), the status indicator's value is distributed in the following way:
  • If the status indicator's value is below 10% (1 out of 10), the first SVG shape (weight 1) is partially filled, depending on the percentage value. For example, if the percentage value of the status indicator is 5, the first SVG shape appears half-full. The rest of the SVG shapes appear empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 10% but below 30%, the first SVG shape (weight 1) is filled, and the second shape (weight 2) is filled only partially, depending on the percentage value. The rest of the SVG shapes in this custom shape appear empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 30% but below 60%, the first two SVG shapes (weight 1 and 2) are filled, and the third SVG shape (weight 3) is filled only partially. The fourth SVG shape (weight 4) appears empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 60% but below 100%, the first three SVG shapes (weight 1, 2, and 3) are filled, but the fourth SVG shape is filled only partially, depending on the percentage value.
  • If the status indicator's value is 100, all four SVG shapes appear filled.
weight.helpDescription:
Weight of the fillable shape, relative to other fillable shapes included in this custom shape.   • If the status indicator's value is below 10% (1 out of 10), the first SVG shape (weight 1) is partially filled, depending on the percentage value. For example, if the percentage value of the status indicator is 5, the first SVG shape appears half-full. The rest of the SVG shapes appear empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 10% but below 30%, the first SVG shape (weight 1) is filled, and the second shape (weight 2) is filled only partially, depending on the percentage value. The rest of the SVG shapes in this custom shape appear empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 30% but below 60%, the first two SVG shapes (weight 1 and 2) are filled, and the third SVG shape (weight 3) is filled only partially. The fourth SVG shape (weight 4) appears empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 60% but below 100%, the first three SVG shapes (weight 1, 2, and 3) are filled, but the fourth SVG shape is filled only partially, depending on the percentage value.
  • If the status indicator's value is 100, all four SVG shapes appear filled.

sap.suite.ui.commons.taccount.TAccount.description: The T account control displays debit and credit entries on a general ledger account. It can be used to visualize the flow of transactions through the accounts where these transactions are stored.
sap.suite.ui.commons.taccount.TAccount.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new TAccount. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getMeasureOfUnit measureOfUnit} : string (default: )
    • {@link #getCollapsed collapsed} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getSubtitle subtitle} : string
    • {@link #getOrderBy orderBy} : string (default: )
    • {@link #getOpening opening} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getOpeningDebit openingDebit} : float (default: 0)
    • {@link #getOpeningCredit openingCredit} : float (default: 0)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getDebit debit} : sap.suite.ui.commons.taccount.TAccountItem[]
    • {@link #getCredit credit} : sap.suite.ui.commons.taccount.TAccountItem[]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.
sap.suite.ui.commons.taccount.TAccount.helpDescription: The T account control displays debit and credit entries on a general ledger account. It can be used to visualize the flow of transactions through the accounts where these transactions are stored.

sap.suite.ui.commons.NoteTakerCard.description: This control allows you to store Note Taker card header and body text.
sap.suite.ui.commons.NoteTakerCard.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new NoteTakerCard. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getHeader header} : string
    • {@link #getBody body} : string
    • {@link #getTimestamp timestamp} : object (default: new Date())
    • {@link #getTags tags} : object (default: [])
    • {@link #getViewAllTrigger viewAllTrigger} : int (default: 1800)
    • {@link #getUid uid} : string
    • {@link #getIsFiltered isFiltered} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getThumbUp thumbUp} : boolean
    • {@link #getThumbDown thumbDown} : boolean
    • {@link #getAllTags allTags} : object (default: [])
    • {@link #getAttachmentFilename attachmentFilename} : string
    • {@link #getAttachmentUrl attachmentUrl} : string
  • Events
    • {@link #event:editNote editNote} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:deleteNote deleteNote} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentClick attachmentClick} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowConnecti.description: This control is used inside the ProcessFlow control to connect process flow node A with process flow node B in respect to the style(x) chosen by the application.
sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowConnecti.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ProcessFlowConnection. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getDrawData drawData} : object[]
    • {@link #getZoomLevel zoomLevel} : sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowZoomLevel (default: Two)
    • {@link #getType type} : sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowConnectionType (default: Normal)
    • {@link #getState state} : sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowConnectionState (default: Regular)
  • Aggregations
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.
sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowConnecti.helpDescription: This control is used inside the ProcessFlow control to connect process flow node A with process flow node B in respect to the style(x) chosen by the application.

drawData.description: This is an array of the following attributes for one element: 1. flowLine (string) - A connection definition where the line should be drawn. A string which defines a course of a flow line. A flow line is a connection between nodes in a process flow control. The string can contain the following characters: - "r" for right, - "t" for top, - "l" for left, - "b" for bottom. 2. targetNodeState (ProcessFlowNodeState) - A copy of the target node status. If the target node is created, the line is solid. If the target node is planned, the line is dashed. 3. displayState (ProcessFlowDisplayState) - Display state of the node. This property defines if the node is displayed regularly, highlighted, or dimmed in combination with a selected visual style of the control. 4. hasArrow (boolean) - Indicates if the line has an arrow on the right end.
drawData.helpDescription: This is an array of the following attributes for one element: 1. flowLine (string) - A connection definition where the line should be drawn. A string which defines a course of a flow line. A flow line is a connection between nodes in a process flow control. The string can contain the following characters: - "r" for right, - "t" for top, - "l" for left, - "b" for bottom. 2. targetNodeState (ProcessFlowNodeState) - A copy of the target node status. If the target node is created, the line is solid. If the target node is planned, the line is dashed. 3. displayState (ProcessFlowDisplayState) - Display state of the node. This property defines if the node is displayed regularly, highlighted, or dimmed in combination with a selected visual style of the control. 4. hasArrow (boolean) - Indicates if the line has an arrow on the right end.

sap.suite.ui.commons.NoteTaker.description: This control allows you to create and store your notes for further reference.
sap.suite.ui.commons.NoteTaker.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new NoteTaker. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getVisibleNotes visibleNotes} : int (default: 2)
    • {@link #getCardViewAllTrigger cardViewAllTrigger} : int (default: 1800)
    • {@link #getFilterCriteria filterCriteria} : object
    • {@link #getAttachmentUploadUrl attachmentUploadUrl} : string
    • {@link #getAttachmentName attachmentName} : string (default: attachment)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getCards cards} : sap.suite.ui.commons.NoteTakerCard[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:addCard addCard} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:deleteCard deleteCard} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:editCard editCard} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentSelect attachmentSelect} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentUploadComplete attachmentUploadComplete} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentDelete attachmentDelete} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentClick attachmentClick} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

The data can be displayed not only in rows but also in tiles that are adjusted to fill the entire horizontal space in a row.
sap.suite.ui.commons.ViewRepeater.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ViewRepeater. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getItemMinWidth itemMinWidth} : int
    • {@link #getResponsive responsive} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getDefaultViewIndex defaultViewIndex} : int (default: 0)
    • {@link #getShowSearchField showSearchField} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowViews showViews} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getExternal external} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getItemHeight itemHeight} : int
    • {@link #getHeight height} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 100%)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getViews views} : sap.suite.ui.commons.RepeaterViewConfiguration[]
  • Associations
    • {@link #getExternalRepresentation externalRepresentation} : (sap.ui.core.ID | sap.ui.core.Control)
  • Events
    • {@link #event:search search} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:changeView changeView} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.commons.RowRepeater#constructor sap.ui.commons.RowRepeater} can be used as well.

The number of columns depends on the parent control's width. If you resize the control, the number of columns may change respectively so that the content tiles can fill the entire space of a row.

sap.suite.ui.commons.MonitoringContent.description: This control is used in a tile or any other place to display numeric values and an icon.
sap.suite.ui.commons.MonitoringContent.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new MonitoringContent. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getValue value} : string
    • {@link #getIconSrc iconSrc} : string
    • {@link #getSize size} : sap.suite.ui.commons.InfoTileSize (default: Auto)
    • {@link #getState state} : sap.suite.ui.commons.LoadState (default: Loaded)
    • {@link #getAnimateTextChange animateTextChange} : boolean (default: true)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getIcon icon} : sap.ui.core.Icon
  • Events
    • {@link #event:press press} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.
sap.suite.ui.commons.MonitoringContent.helpDescription:
Deprecated! Since 1.25 This control has been deprecated in favor of new sap.suite.ui.commons.NumericContent.

sap.suite.ui.commons.KpiTile.description: This control is used in UnifiedThingInspector to display object-related KPIs in a factsheet.
sap.suite.ui.commons.KpiTile.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new KpiTile. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getValue value} : string
    • {@link #getDescription description} : string
    • {@link #getDoubleFontSize doubleFontSize} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getValueUnit valueUnit} : string
    • {@link #getValueScale valueScale} : string
    • {@link #getValueStatus valueStatus} : sap.suite.ui.commons.ValueStatus (default: Neutral)
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.
sap.suite.ui.commons.KpiTile.helpDescription:
Deprecated! Since 1.32 Deprecated. Numeric content or any other standard Fiori control should be used instead.
This control is used in UnifiedThingInspector to display object-related KPIs in a factsheet.

busyIndicatorSize.description: The size of the BusyIndicator. For controls with a width smaller 3rem a sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Small should be used.
